args: *sigh* Our beach trip had its ups and\ndowns, but now that we're home, there's\na sad sense of finality about it all.
I still haven't quite managed to shake\nmy mind out of vacation mode.
I'm quite the same. I may have let myself\nrelax a bit TOO much over the break.
We shall have to redouble our efforts to\nget back to norm—uh? Hello?
Ahhh, I feel so cool—so free!\nThis is heaven!
Why...are you wearing your swimsuit\ninside the castle?
Here we're fretting over still being in\nvacation mode, and this one's yet to\neven entertain the notion it's over.
Try to contain your jealousy. We may be\nback from the beach, but as long as it\nstays this hot out, I'm staying on break.
A rebellion isn't over until the war is won.
*huff* *huff* Phew!\nI finally made it to Alberia!
Sorry, milady, but the jig is up. Your life\nas a fugitive hiding abroad ends today!
Pardon? I distinctly recall her asserting\nthat her vacation time had been cleared\nthrough the appropriate channels.
Yeah, no. I'm afraid she conned you, sir!\nLady Mitsuhide snuck out of her office\nmid-workday and ran for the hills!
Stop making it sound like I'm the villain\nhere. I DID give word that I'd be taking\nsome time off...to Bonnie.
Telling your mouse doesn't get the\nmessage to the rest of us, milady!
Thanks to your disappearance, work has\nbeen piling up left and right. The masses\nwound up swarming my office!
You mean there have been RIOTS as a\nresult? I pray none of you were harmed!
No, we're all fine, thank you. Everyone was\nSUPER angry at first, so I was worried it\nmight turn into a full-blown incident...
But one look at my adorable face, and\neveryone calmed right down! Tee hee. ☆
That's...a feat of diplomacy only you could\npull off, Chitose.
You flatter me, sir. ☆ But just because\nno one got hurt doesn't make it all right!
We're going to light a fire under your tush\nuntil you've worked hard enough to make\nit up to all the citizens you let down!
In agriculture, construction, and industry,\ndid we lose more productivity than any\nother region while I was away?
What? Oh, absolutely. Productivity is way\ndown across the board. Just look at—
Huh? That's strange... If we're comparing it\nto the other regions, we haven't really lost\nany more ground than anyone else.
Mm-hm. And the medical directors?\nWhat do they have to say?
Well... The doctors all seemed pretty\nhappy, actually?
They said that we've lost very few people\nto heat, given how bad the summer's been.\nAnd that other regions have seen worse...
There you have it. What have I said this\nwhole time? Push yourself to work in this\nheat, and you'll just wind up sick.

Which is why I ordered our people to sleep
the summer away, one and all. But nooo,
when the weather's nice, people want to
DO things.
I figured if they're all going to ignore me\nand do whatever they please, I may as\nwell do the same! And so I left.
So you came to Alberia in order to FORCE\nyourself—and by extension, your people—\nto take it easy during this heat wave.
Incidentally, WE'VE all managed to avoid\nsuccumbing to any heat-related illness this\nsummer as well.
I suppose we have. In years past, I often\ngot lightheaded from staying out in the\nsun for too long.
And I've been sunburned more times than\nI can count. Yet this year, I spent my time\nin the shade instead.
I've always felt a lethargy in the late\nsummer weeks, myself, but I've been\ncompletely fine this year.
All despite temperatures being hotter than\never. Hm... Was it truly because we all\nkept to the shade with Mitsuhide?
You're welcome. The whole reason\nsummer breaks started in the first\nplace was to escape the heat, after all.
Mitsuhide... Don't tell me that all that talk\nof rebellion against summer and dragging\nus into your pageant of indolence was—
Actually a deliberate plan to preserve our\nhealth and that of her people?!
Hm, I wonder! What I WILL say is that if\nthis little episode has made any of you\nconverts to easy living, you're welcome.
I... I suppose it has! I cannot deny that you\nhave taught me how to stay cool during the\nsummer months.
And I'll make an effort in years to come to\nlaze about just enough to avoid that usual\nbout of lethargy.
As will I. Thank you, Mitsuhide!
Hah hah haaah! No problemo, my chums.\nNow, if you'll excuse me, I'm overdue for\ntoday's post-midday powernap pre-nap.
Gosh... I had no idea Lady Mitsuhide was\ndoing it all for her people and her friends\nthe entire time.
I know I'VE been working hard all summer.\nMaybe I should spend some time goofing\noff in this nice, cool castle... Ack! NO!
That is NOT why I came all the way here!
Lady Mitsuhideee! You're coming back with\nme to Hinomoto TODAY!
Ugh, weren't you listening? We all just\ndecided that—GAH! Let GO of me!
Lemme go, lemme go, LEMME GOOOOO!
That was...perhaps not the most dignified\nfarewell.
Anyway, one cannot deny that by resisting\nsummer's temptations and staying cool,\nwe all managed to preserve our health.
In that regard, we may have truly taken the\nreins from summer, thanks to Mitsuhide's\nintervention.
Ha ha. I suppose that makes her\nrebellion an unqualified success.\n＂Night time, right time,＂ indeed!
